abstract_ssm:
Time is the first magazine created by Time Inc. and was the impetus to form the publishing company. Time launched its first issue on March 3, 1923. 

The Time Editorial Records contain records from offices and staff from the editorial side of the magazine, not the publishing or business side. Staff represented include managing editors, executive editors, a cover researcher, a senior design coordinator, and a journalist.
